Provenance generation. Unlike in previous work [safavi-etal-2021-negater], negations generated by \uncommon{} come naturally with an explanation via the relationship between the siblings and the target concept. We call these explanations \textbf{negation provenances}. We generate these human-readable phrases by measuring the in-group frequency of shared hypernyms. In particular, we compute a score for each hypernym {{arxiv_2208_09292_FO0057||FO}} that holds for s within the set of siblings sharing phrase f.